ory:Utica Blue Sox players]]\n", "name_user": "Ira Leviton", "label": "safe", "comment": "Deleted a duplicate \"the\".", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richie_Ashburn"}
{"title_page": "2020\u201321 Gonzaga Bulldogs men's basketball team", "text_new": "{{short description|American college basketball season}}\n{{Infobox NCAA team season\n| sport = basketball\n| year = 2020\u201321\n| prev_year = 2019\u201320\n| next_year = 2021\u201322\n| team = Gonzaga Bulldogs\n| logo = Gonzaga Bulldogs wordmark.svg\n| logo_size = \n| logo_alt = \n| image = \n| image_size = \n| image_alt = \n| conference = West Coast Conference\n| short_conf = WCC\n| CoachRank = \n| APRank = \n| record = 0-0\n| conf_record = 0-0\n| head_coach = [[Mark Few]]\n| hc_year = 22nd\n| asst_coach1 = [[Tommy Lloyd]]\n| ac1_year = 20th\n| asst_coach2 = [[Brian Michaelson]]\n| ac2_year = 8th\n| asst_coach3 = [[Roger Powell (basketball)|Roger Powell]]\n| ac3_year = 2nd\n| captain = \n| captain_year = \n| captain2 = \n| captain2_year =\n| arena = [[McCarthey Athletic Center]]\n| champion = \n| tourney = \n| tourney_result = \n}}\n{{2020\u201321 West Coast Conference men's basketball standings}} \nThe '''2020\u201321 Gonzaga Bulldogs men's basketball team''' represented [[Gonzaga University]], located in [[Spokane, Washington]], in the [[2020\u201321 NCAA Division I men's basketball season]]. The team is led by head coach [[Mark Few]], in his 22nd season as head coach. This is the Bulldogs' 17th season at the on-campus [[McCarthey Athletic Center]] and 41st season as a member of the [[West Coast Conference]].\n\n==Previous season==\n{{main|2019\u201320 Gonzaga Bulldogs men's basketball team}}\n\nThey Bulldogs finished the season 31\u20132, 15\u20131 in WCC play to be WCC regular season champions. They then defeated [[2019\u201320 San Francisco Dons men's basketball team|San Francisco]] and [[2019\u201320 Saint Mary's Gaels men's basketball team|Saint Mary's]] to be champions of the [[2020 West Coast Conference Men's Basketball Tournament|WCC Tournament]]. They earned the WCC's automatic bid to the [[2020 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|NCAA Tournament]]. However, all postseason play, including the NCAA Tournament, was cancelled amid the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|2020 coronavirus pandemic]]. The Bulldogs finished #2 in the final AP and Coaches poll.\n\n==Offseason==\n\n===Coaching Changes===\n====Departures====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\" border=\"1\"\n! Name\n! Position\n! Year at<br>Gonzaga\n! [[Alma Mater]] (year)\n!! class=\"unsortable\" | Reason for Departure\n|-\n| {{sortname|||nolink=1}}\n|| \n|| \n|| \n|| \n|}\n\n====Additions to Staff====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\" border=\"1\"\n! Name\n! Position\n! Year at<br>Gonzaga\n! [[Alma Mater]] (year)\n!! class=\"unsortable\" | Previous Job\n|-\n| {{sortname|||nolink=1}}\n|| \n|| \n|| \n|| \n|}\n\n===Player Departures===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\" border=\"1\"\n! Name\n! Number\n! Pos.\n! Height\n! Weight\n! Year\n! Hometown\n!! class=\"unsortable\" | Reason for Departure\n|-\n| {{sortname|Killian|Tillie}}\n|| {{nts|33}}\n|| [[Forward (basketball)|F]]\n|| {{sort|82|6'10\"}}\n|| 220\n|| {{sort|4|Senior}}\n|| [[Cagnes-sur-Mer]], [[France]]\n|| Graduated\n|-\n| {{sortname|Admon|Gilder}}\n|| {{nts|1}}\n|| [[Guard (basketball)|G]]\n|| {{sort|76|6'4\"}}\n|| 200\n|| {{sort|4.5|Senior}} ([[Redshirt (college sports)|Redshirt]])\n|| [[Dallas|Dallas, Texas]]\n|| Graduated\n|-\n| {{sortname|Ryan|Woolridge|nolink=1}}\n|| {{nts|4}}\n|| [[Guard (basketball)|G]]\n|| {{sort|75|6'3\"}}\n|| 175\n|| {{sort|4.5|Senior}} ([[Redshirt (college sports)|Redshirt]])\n|| [[Mansfield, Texas]]\n|| Graduated\n|}\n\n===Incoming transfers===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\" border=\"1\"\n! Name\n! Number\n! Pos.\n! Height\n! Weight\n! Year\n! Hometown\n!! class=\"unsortable\" | Previous<br>School\n!! class=\"unsortable\" | Years<br>Remaining\n!! class=\"unsortable\" | Date<br>Eligible\n|-\n| {{sortname|Aaron|Cook|nolink=y}}\n|| {{nts|--}}\n|| [[Guard (basketball)|G]]\n|| {