21 West Coast Conference men's basketball standings}} \nThe '''2020\u201321 Gonzaga Bulldogs men's basketball team''' represented [[Gonzaga University]], located in [[Spokane, Washington]], in the [[2020\u201321 NCAA Division I men's basketball season]]. The team is led by head coach [[Mark Few]], in his 22nd season as head coach. This is the Bulldogs' 17th season at the on-campus [[McCarthey Athletic Center]] and 41st season as a member of the [[West Coast Conference]].\n\n==Previous season==\n{{main|2019\u201320 Gonzaga Bulldogs men's basketball team}}\n\nThey Bulldogs finished the season 31\u20132, 15\u20131 in WCC play to be WCC regular season champions. They then defeated [[2019\u201320 San Francisco Dons men's basketball team|San Francisco]] and [[2019\u201320 Saint Mary's Gaels men's basketball team|Saint Mary's]] to be champions of the [[2020 West Coast Conference Men's Basketball Tournament|WCC Tournament]]. They earned the WCC's automatic bid to the [[2020 NCAA Division I Men's Basketball Tournament|NCAA Tournament]]. However, all postseason play, including the NCAA Tournament, was cancelled amid the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic in the United States|2020 coronavirus pandemic]]. The Bulldogs finished #2 in the final AP and Coaches poll.\n\n==Offseason==\n\n===Coaching Changes===\n====Departures====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\" border=\"1\"\n! Name\n! Position\n! Year at<br>Gonzaga\n! [[Alma Mater]] (year)\n!! class=\"unsortable\" | Reason for Departure\n|-\n| {{sortname|||nolink=1}}\n|| \n|| \n|| \n|| \n|}\n\n====Additions to Staff====\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\" border=\"1\"\n! Name\n! Position\n! Year at<br>Gonzaga\n! [[Alma Mater]] (year)\n!! class=\"unsortable\" | Previous Job\n|-\n| {{sortname|||nolink=1}}\n|| \n|| \n|| \n|| \n|}\n\n===Player Departures===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" style=\"font-size:90%;\" border=\"1\"\n! Name\n! Number\n! Pos.\n! Height\n! Weight\n! Year\n! Hometown\n!! 