Hennard (25) || [[St. Joseph, Missouri|Missouri (St. Joseph)]] || Police responded to a report of a stolen vehicle and pursued two suspects on foot. One of them, Hennard, turned and shot at officers, who returned fire.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kctv5.com/story/36656398/woman-killed-after-shooting-at-police-in-st-joe |title=Woman killed after shooting at police in St. Joe | first=Daniel  | last=Barnett | publisher=KCTV | accessdate=1 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.komu.com/news/woman-killed-after-shooting-at-police/|title=Woman killed after shooting at police |publisher=KOMU-TV |accessdate=1 November 2017}}</ref><ref>{{cite news | url=http://www.newspressnow.com/news/local_news/no-charges-in-death-of-woman-shot-by-officer/article_1e93a305-a478-5e8e-a14e-3dd0b5cdd423.html | title=No charges in death of woman shot by officer | date=January 10, 2018 | accessdate=27 March 2018 | publisher=St. Joseph News-Press}}</ref>\n|-\n|2017-10-20 || Armando Frank (44) || [[Marksville, Louisiana|Louisiana (Markville)]] || Frank was sitting on his tractor in a parking lot when sheriff\u2019s deputies came to him and ordered him off, saying they had a warrant for his arrest (on trespassing). Frank asked to see the warrant, which the deputies did not have with them. They continued to demand, he continued to refuse. The deputies then dragged Frank off the tractor. One put him in a chokehold for several minutes, asphyxiating Frank. (One of the deputies shot a Taser at the other during the arrest.)<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.theroot.com/video-louisiana-cops-strangle-black-man-to-death-for-a-1828091116 |title=Video: Louisiana Cops Strangle Black Man to Death for Asking to See Arrest Warrant |date=3 August 2018 |publisher=The Root |access-date=4 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.kalb.com/content/news/Pathologist-Armando-Frank-died-from-asphyxia-during-arrest-struggle-489669991.html |title=Pathologist: Armando Frank died from 'asphyxia' during a