lmography-by-production-number/ |accessdate=20 September 2018}}</ref>\n! scope=\"col\" | Notes\n|-\n| February 19, 1938 || [[The Captain and the Kids (MGM animated series)|The Captain and the Kids]] || ''Cleaning House'' || Robert Allen || style=\"text-align: right\"| 2 || First ''The Captain and the Kids'' cartoon.<br />First cartoon to be produced in-house by [[Metro Goldwyn Mayer]] with [[Fred Quimby]] as producer. \n|-\n| April 2, 1938 || The Captain and the Kids || ''Blue Monday'' ||  [[William Hanna]] || style=\"text-align: right\"| 3 ||\n|-\n| April 16, 1938 || The Captain and the Kids || ''Poultry Pirates'' || [[Friz Freleng]] || style=\"text-align: right\"| 5 ||\n|-\n| April 30, 1938 || The Captain and the Kids || ''The Captain's Pup'' || Robert Allen || style=\"text-align: right\"| 4 ||\n|-\n| June 25, 1938 || The Captain and the Kids || ''A Day at the Beach'' || Friz Freleng || style=\"text-align: right\"| 10 ||\n|-\n| July 16, 1938 || The Captain and the Kids || ''What a Lion'' || William Hanna || style=\"text-align: right\"| 12 ||\n|-\n| August 6, 1938 || The Captain and the Kids || ''The Pygmy Hunt'' || Friz Freleng || style=\"text-align: right\"| 7 || \n|-\n| September 3, 1938 || The Captain and the Kids || ''Old Smokey'' || William Hanna || style=\"text-align: right\"| 6 ||\n|-\n| September 17, 1938 || The Captain and the Kids || ''Buried Treasure'' || Robert Allen || style=\"text-align: right\"| 11 ||\n|-\n| October 1, 1938 ||The Captain and the Kids || ''The Winning Ticket'' || Unknown || style=\"text-align: right\"| 13 ||\n|-\n| October 15, 1938 || The Captain and the Kids || ''Honduras Hurricane'' || William Hanna || style=\"text-align: right\"| 14 ||\n|-\n| December 17, 1938 || The Captain and the Kids || ''The Captain's Christmas'' || Friz Freleng || style=\"text-align: right\"| 9  || Filmed in Technicolor\n|-\n| January 14, 1939 || [[The Captain and the Kids]] || ''Petunia Natural Park'' || Friz Freleng || style=\"text-align: right\"| 15 ||Fil